<paragraph blockId="142.[189,1399,1894,2027]" pageId="142" pageNumber="143">
Species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hess" authorityYear="1964" box="[318,463,1895,1920]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiacanthidae" genus="Dermocoma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="142" pageNumber="143" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[318,463,1895,1920]" italics="true" pageId="142" pageNumber="143">Dermocoma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with large LAPs displaying a well-developed vertical striation; two moderately well-defined spurs on outer proximal and inner distal edge, dorsal one of which slightly larger and better defined; up to four relatively large spine articulations; ridge on inner side with strongly widened and dorsalwards pointing dorsal tip.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
